content.description:
Dirty Hummingbird follows the obvious left-facing dihedral.

Easily protected, moderate laybacks, hand jams, lichen smears and even some finger locks get you to the top of the formation. Although overgrown, it's a fun setting. We were able to do it in a single pitch with a 70m, would probably have to simul or do two pitches with anything less.

Easy walk-offs to either side, I always go down the slabs on the climber's left.
content.protection: Standard Rack, pretty much eats up whatever you want to throw at it.
content.location: Head south down Stony Creek past the intersection of it and Woodward Creek. The route is the obvious left facing dihedral on the east side of the creek. Some creek navigating required, watch your step :)
